snippet.textDisplay: I have not played any of the Digimon games.  I loved the anime.  It was one of my favorites to watch growing up.  I watched the first two seasons, but i stopped once the third season started.  I felt that Toei really strayed away from what made the first two seasons great.  Like any Toei anime, Digimon has a lot of episodes, but it is well worth the watch.  I would try to stay away from watching the third and fourth seasons as they were pretty bad.

snippet.textDisplay: I've actually never really paid too much attention to the Digimon universe, probably because I was too busy with Pokemon already at the time. The most I did was watch a couple episodes here and there when it happened to play on TV. I heard the games were solid, especially the Digimon World games, as well as the music in the series. Cyber Sleuth came out recently here and it's been well received. The game was made by Media Vision (Wild Arms series) so I'm not surprised. The soundtrack is also very impressive, which again is not a surprise considering Masafumi Takada (killer7, God Hand, No More Heroes to name a few) is behind it.
